## Survey Builder — a Node.js/Express app

A logged-in user creates surveys with multiple questions, shares a public response link, and views collected responses in a table. Data is stored in **SQLite** (auto-created on first run — nothing to install separately).

### Files created

```
package.json           Dependency manifest
server.js              Express app: auth, survey CRUD, public responses
db.js                  SQLite connection + schema (users, surveys, questions, responses, answers)
views/
  partials/head.ejs    Shared header/nav
  partials/foot.ejs
  login.ejs  register.ejs
  dashboard.ejs        Your surveys
  new-survey.ejs       Dynamic question builder
  survey.ejs           Share link + responses table
  respond.ejs          Public response form
  error.ejs
public/
  styles.css           Styling
  new-survey.js        Client-side add/remove question logic
README.md  .gitignore
```

### Key features
- **Auth**: register / login with `bcryptjs`-hashed passwords, sessions persisted in SQLite (`express-session` + `connect-sqlite3`).
- **Survey creation**: title, description, and any number of questions — short text, long text, or multiple choice (options one-per-line). Questions are added/removed dynamically in the browser.
- **Public link**: each survey gets a random `public_id`; `/s/:publicId` is answerable by anyone, no login.
- **Responses table**: the survey page renders every response as a row, one column per question.
- **Safety**: parameterized prepared statements throughout, EJS auto-escaping, multi-row inserts wrapped in transactions, owner-scoped access checks on survey pages.

### How to run locally (port 5055)

```bash
npm install
npm start
```

Then open <http://localhost:5055>. Port is configurable via `PORT` (defaults to 5055). Full instructions and a route table are in `README.md`.

