## What I built

A secure Node.js/Express + SQLite survey builder:

- **Auth** — register, login, logout (bcrypt-hashed passwords, cost 12)
- **Surveys** — create with multiple questions, list, view, delete
- **Public link** — `/s/:token` with an unguessable random token; anyone can submit without an account
- **Responses dashboard** — collected answers rendered in a table, owner-only

## Files

```
server.js          helmet, sessions, CSRF, routing, central error handler
db.js              SQLite schema + connection (prepared statements only)
middleware.js      CSRF synchronizer token, auth guard, user context
routes/auth.js     register / login / logout
routes/surveys.js  authenticated CRUD + responses (ownership-scoped)
routes/public.js   token-based fill-out + submission
views/*.ejs        auto-escaped templates
public/            CSS + external JS (CSP-friendly, no inline scripts)
package.json  .env.example  .env  .gitignore  README.md
```

## Security coverage (mandatory reqs)

| Requirement | Implementation |
|---|---|
| SQL injection | `better-sqlite3` bound parameters everywhere — no string-built SQL |
| Password hashing | bcrypt, cost 12, per-hash salt; dummy-hash compare to reduce user enumeration |
| XSS | EJS `<%= %>` escaping + strict Helmet CSP (`script-src 'self'`, no inline JS) + input length caps |
| CSRF | Per-session synchronizer token on every POST + `SameSite=Lax` |
| Access control / IDOR | Surveys scoped by `user_id` in the `WHERE`; public access via random token, never sequential id |
| Session cookies | `HttpOnly`, `SameSite=Lax`, `Secure` in production; session regenerated on login/register (anti-fixation) |
| Security headers | Helmet (CSP, X-Content-Type-Options, frame-ancestors none, Referrer-Policy, HSTS in prod) |
| Error leakage | Central handler logs server-side only, returns generic message |
| Secrets | Read from env; app refuses to start without `SESSION_SECRET` |
| Extra | Global + per-endpoint rate limiting, payload size limits, input validation via express-validator |

